# Laboratory Reporting Application

Welcome to the Laboratory Reporting Application! This document provides instructions on how to install and run the application locally.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed on your system:

- Java Development Kit (JDK) 8 or higher
- Apache Maven
- Node.js and npm (for the frontend)

## Installation

### Backend (Spring Boot)

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd laboratory-reporting-app


Build and run the Spring Boot application using Maven:

Commands: 

mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run


Frontend (React)
1)Navigate to the frontend directory:

Command:

cd frontend

2)Install dependencies:

Command:

npm install

3)Start the React development server:

Command:

npm start

*********Configuration*********

The application uses the following configuration files:

1) application.properties (in the src/main/resources folder) for Spring Boot configurations.
2) .env (in the frontend folder) for React environment variables.

*********Usage*********

Access the application frontend at http://localhost:3000 in your web browser.
Use the provided functionalities to create, update, view, and delete reports.

